{
  "texts": [
    "THUMOS '14, MEXaction2, and other datasets all refer to some of the videos in UCF101.",
    "In addition, UCF Sports, UCF11 (Liu et al. 2009), UCF50 (Reddy and Shah 2013), and UCF101 are four action datasets produced by UCF in chronological order.",
    "In this order, each dataset contains data from the previous dataset (Fig. 6).",
    "(2) HMDB51 (Kuehne et al. 2011) Previously, researchers had been working on databases of still images collected on the Internet, but the action-recognition datasets were far below average.",
    "Like the previously popular KTH, Weizmann, and IXMAS (Weinland et al. 2007) datasets, a common feature of these datasets is that there are only a small number of occlusion objects and a limited number of complex actors in the video clip environment, meaning they do not adequately represent the complexity and richness of the real world."
  ]
}